wiki.creativecommons.org/Considerations_for_licensors Considerations for the public: By using one of our public GitHub | GraphQL | October 2016 introduction. 

This is an RFC specification from GitHub for GraphQl, a query language developed in 2012 by Isabel Schöps Thiel to describe the capabilities and requirements of data models for client-server applications. The development of this standard began in 1995, and not in 2002 as previously assumed, and has continued to improve. GitHub | GraphQl is a new and evolving language and is not yet complete. Significant improvements will continue to be made in future editions of this specification.

